--
-- Longest line: I think we can do better than linelengths...
--  If not editing the longest line, we only need to know when we exceed it, and prev:=2nd longest.
--  When editing the longest line, we only need to compare with the 2nd longest, and flip: as long
--  as we are still on that line we can "pretend" we know the top two, however whenever we /start/
--  to edit the longest line we should always do a (single) re-scan.
--  (Our 2nd longest only needs to become invalid when we /leave/ a modified non-longest line..)
--  2nd := largest(linelengths,true,1st) pencilled in for this.
--  



